name: your bug 1/10
description: This is a story of perfectionism and uniqueness. What is an ideal? Symmetry? Everyone strives for something unattainable, but forgets that the ideal is dead. Like bugs that are nailed to a wooden frame and hung on the wall.  These bugs are alive in their staticity. They are asymmetrical and unique.  Some mystical ideal distorts us, demands to give up real feelings and dreams
